## Environment-Specific Examples

### Development (Local)

```bash
# .env.dev
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/ecobook_dev
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=postgres
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=dev_password
OAUTH2_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=dev_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_dev_gemini_key
IMAGE_STORAGE_PATH=/tmp/ecobook_uploads
LOGGING_LEVEL_COM_ECOBOOK=DEBUG
```

### Staging (Pre-Production)

```bash
# .env.staging
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://staging-db.ecobook.internal/ecobook
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=ecobook_staging
OAUTH2_GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://staging-api.ecobook.com/api/v1/auth/callback
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_staging_gemini_key
IMAGE_STORAGE_TYPE=s3
IMAGE_STORAGE_S3_BUCKET=ecobook-staging-materiais
LOGGING_LEVEL_COM_ECOBOOK=INFO
```

### Production

```bash
# .env.production
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://prod-db.ecobook.internal/ecobook
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=ecobook_prod
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=${DATABASE_PASSWORD_SECRET}  # From secrets manager
OAUTH2_GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://api.ecobook.com/api/v1/auth/callback
GEMINI_API_KEY=${GEMINI_API_KEY_SECRET}  # From secrets manager
IMAGE_STORAGE_TYPE=s3
IMAGE_STORAGE_S3_BUCKET=ecobook-materiais-prod
LOGGING_LEVEL_COM_ECOBOOK=WARN
```

---

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Backend Setup

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/JoaoVitorOL/EcoBookAi.git
cd EcoBookAi

# Copy .env template
cp .env.example .env

# Edit .env with your values
nano .env

# Install dependencies (Maven)
mvn clean install

# Start backend server
mvn spring-boot:run
# Server runs on http://localhost:8080
```

### 2. Android Setup

```bash
# In Android Studio:
# 1. File → New → Project from Version Control
# 2. Paste: https://github.com/JoaoVitorOL/EcoBookAi.git
# 3. Download google-services.json from Firebase Console
# 4. Place file in: app/google-services.json
# 5. Update ANDROID_API_BASE_URL in build.gradle
# 6. Build & Run on emulator/device
```

### 3. Database Setup

```bash
# Create PostgreSQL database
createdb ecobook_ia

# Run schema creation
psql ecobook_ia < specs/001-ecobook-core/database-schema.sql

# Verify tables created
psql ecobook_ia -c "\dt"
```

### 4. Get API Keys

- **Google OAuth2**: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
- **Gemini API Key**: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikeys
- **Firebase**: https://console.firebase.google.com

---

## Security Best Practices

1. ✅ **Never commit .env** — Add to .gitignore
2. ✅ **Use secrets manager** in production (AWS Secrets Manager, Kubernetes Secrets, etc.)
3. ✅ **Rotate API keys** regularly
4. ✅ **Use HTTPS** in production (not HTTP)
5. ✅ **Restrict CORS** to trusted domains
6. ✅ **Log sensitive data** minimally (no passwords, tokens in logs)

---

## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| "Connection refused" to PostgreSQL | Check `SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL`, ensure PostgreSQL running locally |
| "Invalid OAuth2 credentials" | Verify `OAUTH2_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` and `OAUTH2_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` match Google Console |
| "Gemini API Key invalid" | Verify key from https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikeys (not from Cloud Console) |
| "Firebase service account not found" | Ensure `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` path is correct |
| "Image upload fails" | Verify `IMAGE_STORAGE_PATH` exists and is writable; check disk space |
